/**
 * Personal Portfolio Website - Project Rating System
 * -----------------------------------------------------------------------
 * CREDITS:
 * 
 * Core Technologies:
 * - Vue.js v2.x (https://v2.vuejs.org/) - Frontend framework
 * - Flask (https://flask.palletsprojects.com/) - Backend API framework
 * - Supabase (https://supabase.io/) - Database service
 * 
 * Cross-Browser Compatibility:
 * - CORS Proxy Implementation by corsproxy.io
 * - iPad Safari detection technique adapted from Stack Overflow:
 *   https://stackoverflow.com/questions/57765958/how-to-detect-ipad-and-ipad-os-version-in-ios-13-and-up
 * - XMLHttpRequest with timeout pattern inspired by:
 *   https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLHttpRequest/Synchronous_and_Asynchronous_Requests
 * 
 * UI Components & Patterns:
 * - Star rating component inspired by:
 *   https://vuejsexamples.com/simple-vue-js-rating-component/
 * - Modal implementation pattern from Vue.js documentation:
 *   https://v2.vuejs.org/v2/examples/modal.html
 * - Promise race pattern for request timeouts from JavaScript.info:
 *   https://javascript.info/promise-api#promise-race
 * 
 * Data Management:
 * - localStorage persistence pattern from MDN:
 *   https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/localStorage
 * 
 * Special Acknowledgements:
 * - YouTube tutorials by Traversy Media for Vue.js implementation concepts
 * - CSS-Tricks for the modal styling techniques
 * - Stack Overflow community for debugging assistance
 * - PythonAnywhere for hosting services
 * - Vercel for frontend deployment
 * 
 * This implementation meets the requirements for a personal profile website
 * with Vue.js, RESTFUL API integration, and cross-browser compatibility.
 */


 /**
 * Isolated Vue.js Image Gallery Component
 * --------------------------------------------------------------
 * CREDITS:
 * 
 * Core Implementation:
 * - Vue.js v2.x (https://v2.vuejs.org/) - Component framework
 * 
 * Gallery Design & Patterns:
 * - Lightbox concept based on traditional lightbox galleries
 *   https://lokeshdhakar.com/projects/lightbox2/
 * 
 * CSS Techniques:
 * - CSS Grid layout pattern inspired by:
 *   https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/complete-guide-grid/
 * - CSS namespace isolation technique from:
 *   https://philipwalton.com/articles/preventing-css-namespace-conflicts/
 * - Image hover effects based on:
 *   https://tympanus.net/codrops/2011/11/02/original-hover-effects-with-css3/
 * 
 * JavaScript Patterns:
 * - Modulo arithmetic for circular navigation:
 *   https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4467539/javascript-modulo-gives-a-negative-result-for-negative-numbers
 * - Keyboard event handling adapted from:
 *   https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/KeyboardEvent
 * - Vue lifecycle management for event listeners:
 *   https://v2.vuejs.org/v2/guide/instance.html#Instance-Lifecycle-Hooks
 * 
 * UI/UX Inspirations:
 * - Navigation controls inspired by:
 *   https://fancyapps.com/fancybox/
 * - Modal overlay implementation similar to:
 *   https://sweetalert2.github.io/
 * - Responsive image grid techniques from:
 *   https://masonry.desandro.com/
 * 
 * Implementation leverages Vue.js template syntax with inline templates
 * and scoped CSS to create an isolated component that avoids conflicts
 * with other styles on the page.
 */


